                            <comment id="433656" author="adilger" created="Sat, 2 Nov 2024 00:25:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is at least partly implemented by patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/54341&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/54341&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;tt&gt;&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17628&quot; title=&quot;add option to restrict lfs setstripe&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17628&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17628&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lfs: add lfs_setstripe admin restrict&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;), which prevents users from setting &lt;b&gt;any&lt;/b&gt; parameters with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs setstripe&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.  However, that is a &quot;soft&quot; restriction that can be overridden by application libraries, while this should probably be implemented as an RBAC control on a nodemap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
